cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.DM. 

This paper deals with spatial logics designed for qualitative spatial representation and reasoning in AI, which suggests that cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The addition of connectedness predicates also involves logical reasoning, which makes cs.LO a likely sub-category as well. The paper also discusses computational complexity, which suggests that cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CG (computational geometry) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves some form of constraint satisfaction, which could make cs.DM (discrete mathematics) a possible sub-category as well.
